-- Renault Plans $307 Million Turkish Engine Investment, Sabah Says
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-09-17T10:45:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-17/renault-plans-307-million-turkish-engine-investment-sabah-says.html
Renault SA (RNO) , which makes seven car
models in Turkey, will invest 234 million euros ($307 million)
in an engine production facility at its plant there,  Sabah 
reported.  Gasoline engines will be produced for Renault’s new Clio 4
model, which has an 898-cc power unit, the newspaper said,
citing Tarik Tunalioglu, the chief executive officer of  Oyak-
Renault Otomobil Fabrikalari AS , Renault’s joint venture with
Turkey’s Oyak Group.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net  